Authors: Slough J.
Author full names: Slough, John (6701512583)
Title: Plasma MagnetoShells (PMS) for Orbit Insertion on Deep-Space Planetary Missions
Affiliations: MSNW LLC, 16436 SE 39th PL, Bellevue, 98008, WA, United States
Authors with affiliations: Slough J., MSNW LLC, 16436 SE 39th PL, Bellevue, 98008, WA, United States
Funding Texts: Plasma MagnetoShell (PMS) Aerocapture is an innovative approach that has been developed by MSNW with funding support from the NASA Innovative Advanced Concepts (NIAC) program, that would enable low-cost, low-risk aerocapture for a range of Earth and deep space missions. The concept to be described and detailed here is the deployment of a coil set to produce a dipolar magnetic field that is filled with a plasma to provide the necessary impediment to the atmospheric flow and thereby produce the desired drag for braking. It is referred to as a Plasma MagnetoShell (PMS). An array of such “magnetospheric parachutes” at high altitude over Mars is depicted in Fig.1. The advantages of PMS are many. Frictional heating is no longer a concern.
Publisher: IEEE Computer Society
